  "html": "<div class=\"schola\"><h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Etymology_2\">Etymology</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=schola&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: Etymology\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3><p>From <span class=\"etyl\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ancient_Greek\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Ancient Greek\">Ancient Greek</a></span> <i class=\"polytonic mention\" lang=\"grc\"><a href=\"/wiki/%CF%83%CF%87%CE%BF%CE%BB%CE%AE#Ancient_Greek\" title=\"&#x3C3;&#x3C7;&#x3BF;&#x3BB;&#x3AE;\">&#x3C3;&#x3C7;&#x3BF;&#x3BB;&#x3AE;</a></i> <span class=\"mention-gloss-paren annotation-paren\">(</span><span lang=\"grc-Latn\" class=\"mention-tr tr Latn\">skhol&#x1E17;</span><span class=\"mention-gloss-paren annotation-paren\">)</span>.\n</p><h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Pronunciation\">Pronunciation</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=schola&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: Pronunciation\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3><ul><li><span class=\"ib-brac qualifier-brac\">(</span><span class=\"ib-content qualifier-content\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Classical_Latin\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Classical Latin\">Classical</a></span><span class=\"ib-brac qualifier-brac\">)</span> <a href=\"/wiki/Wiktionary:International_Phonetic_Alphabet\" title=\"Wiktionary:International Phonetic Alphabet\">IPA</a><sup>(<a href=\"/wiki/Appendix:Latin_pronunciation\" title=\"Appendix:Latin pronunciation\">key</a>)</sup>: <span class=\"IPA\">/&#x2C8;sk&#x2B0;o.la/</span>, <span class=\"IPA\">[&#x2C8;sk&#x2B0;&#x254;.&#x26B;&#x32A;a]</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"ib-brac qualifier-brac\">(</span><span class=\"ib-content qualifier-content\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ecclesiastical_Latin\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Ecclesiastical Latin\">Ecclesiastical</a></span><span class=\"ib-brac qualifier-brac\">)</span> <a href=\"/wiki/Wiktionary:International_Phonetic_Alphabet\" title=\"Wiktionary:International Phonetic Alphabet\">IPA</a><sup>(<a href=\"/wiki/Appendix:Latin_pronunciation\" title=\"Appendix:Latin pronunciation\">key</a>)</sup>: <span class=\"IPA\">/&#x2C8;sko.la/</span>, <span class=\"IPA\">[&#x2C8;sk&#x254;&#x2D0;.la]</span></li></ul><h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Noun_2\">Noun</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=schola&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: Noun\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3><p><strong class=\"Latn headword\" lang=\"la\">schola</strong>&#xA0;<span class=\"gender\"><abbr title=\"feminine gender\">f</abbr></span> (<i>genitive</i> <b class=\"Latn\" lang=\"la\"><a href=\"/wiki/scholae#Latin\" title=\"scholae\">scholae</a></b>); <i><a href=\"/wiki/Appendix:Latin_first_declension\" title=\"Appendix:Latin first declension\">first declension</a></i>\n</p><ol><li>Leisure time given to <a href=\"/wiki/learning\" title=\"learning\">learning</a>; <a href=\"/wiki/schooltime\" title=\"schooltime\">schooltime</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/classtime\" title=\"classtime\">classtime</a>.\n<ul><li><b>c.&#xA0;<span style=\"font-variant:small-caps;\">ad</span>&#xA0;65</b>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Seneca_the_Younger\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Seneca the Younger\">Seneca</a>, <i><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Epistulae_morales_ad_Lucilium\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Epistulae morales ad Lucilium\">Moral Letters to Lucilius</a></i>, <a href=\"https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Moral_letters_to_Lucilius/Letter_106\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"s:Moral letters to Lucilius/Letter 106\">CVI</a>.\n<dl><dd><span style=\"font-variant:small-caps;\">non vit&#xE6; sed <b>schol&#xE6;</b> discimvs</span>\n<dl><dd>We learn [such literature] not for life but for <b>schooltime</b>.</dd></dl></dd></dl></li></ul></li>\n<li>A <a href=\"/wiki/school\" title=\"school\">school</a>; a place for <a href=\"/wiki/learning\" title=\"learning\">learning</a> or <a href=\"/wiki/instruction\" title=\"instruction\">instruction</a>.\n<ul><li><b>1804</b> Jun 12, <i>Oberdeutsche Allgemeine Litteraturzeitung</i>, No.&#xA0;70, p.&#xA0;1119\n<dl><dd><span style=\"font-variant:small-caps;\">non <b>schol&#xE6;</b> sed vit&#xE6; discendvm est</span>\n<dl><dd>We must learn not for <b>school</b> but for life.</dd></dl></dd></dl></li></ul></li>\n<li>A <a href=\"/wiki/student_body\" title=\"student body\">student body</a>; the <a href=\"/wiki/disciple\" title=\"disciple\">disciples</a> of a teacher.</li>\n<li>A <a href=\"/wiki/sect\" title=\"sect\">sect</a>; body of followers of a <a href=\"/wiki/teacher\" title=\"teacher\">teacher</a> or <a href=\"/wiki/system\" title=\"system\">system</a>, such as the Praetorian guard.</li>\n<li>An <a href=\"/wiki/art\" title=\"art\">art</a> <a href=\"/wiki/gallery\" title=\"gallery\">gallery</a>.</li></ol><h4><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Declension\">Declension</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=schola&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" title=\"Edit section: Declension\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h4><p><a href=\"/wiki/Appendix:Latin_first_declension\" title=\"Appendix:Latin first declension\">First-declension</a> noun.<style data-mw-deduplicate=\"TemplateStyles:r50505018\">.mw-parser-output .inflection-table-la .corner-header,.mw-parser-output .inflection-table-la .number-header,.mw-parser-output .inflection-table-la .case-header{font-style:italic}.mw-parser-output .inflection-table-la .corner-header,.mw-parser-output .inflection-table-la .number-header{background-color:#549EA0}.mw-parser-output .inflection-table-la .case-header{background-color:#40E0D0}